						               													<description>Cryptic Words is a word guessing game for two players. Each player thinks of a secret word and hides it in plain sight for their opponent to guess using common clues.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is played in rounds until someone hits or exceeds 30 points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In each round, players first grab six hexagonal letter tiles and secretly think of a 3- to 8-letter words and encode and it using a proprietary tracking form. They write down the codes for their word, shuffle their tiles and swap them with their opponent.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Using the game board, players arrange the tiles in any order front of them. The deduction phase starts.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players take turns rolling two dice and either perform an action on doubles or strategically pose a question. The question will try to pinpoint letters in the opponent's word. Both players must answer the question. The answer may reveal a letter in an opponent's word.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
